div.h1: Context Switch: The ESP Swap Metamorphosis
div.p: mov esp, [new_pcb + ESP_OFFSET] One instruction changes identity

g.text: BEFORE Process A is being saved
AFTER Process B is being restored
Control flow before swap Stack A
Control flow after swap Stack B

div.p: Phase: Saving Process A push ebx; push esi; push edi; push ebp; pushfd ESP moves DOWN into A's stack with each push

g.text: Process A Kernel Stack (8 KB alloc)

div.p: push ebx ; EBX saved push esi ; ESI saved push edi ; EDI saved push ebp ; EBP saved pushfd ; EFLAGS saved ; ESP now = old_ctx ptr - 20 mov [old_ctx+ESP_OFF], esp ; SAVE A's ESP
Process A's full context is now frozen on its stack. Next: one instruction ends Process A's reign.

ul.li: Every push/pop Stack A AFTER this instruction:
Every push/pop Stack B The CPU identity has changed. The function that "returns" is NOT the same process that "called" it.

div.p: offset 0: edi offset 4: esi offset 8: ebx offset 12: ebp offset 16: esp loaded into ESP offset 20: eip where B will resume offset 24: eflags

p.strong: What the CPU does NOT do automatically:

ul.li: Save/restore GP registers (EBX, ESI, EDI, EBP)
Load new CR3 All of this is YOUR code, before/after this instruction.

div.p: Phase: Restoring Process B popfd; pop ebp; pop edi; pop esi; pop ebx; ret ESP moves UP through B's stack with each pop

g.text: Process B Kernel Stack (8 KB alloc)

div.p: ; ESP is now on B's stack popfd ; Restore B's EFLAGS (IF=1 interrupts ON) pop ebp ; Restore B's EBP pop edi ; Restore B's EDI pop esi ; Restore B's ESI pop ebx ; Restore B's EBX ret ; Pop B's saved EIP jump to B's resume point
Process B resumes exactly where it was preempted. It never knew it stopped.

SAVE PHASE running on Stack A (green = Stack A) asm context_switch_asm: ; called with (old_ctx, new_ctx) on Stack A push ebx ; ESP-=4 Stack A [16] push esi ; ESP-=4 Stack A [12] push edi ; ESP-=4 Stack A [08] push ebp ; ESP-=4 Stack A [04] pushfd ; ESP-=4 Stack A [00] mov eax, [esp + 24] ; eax = old_ctx ptr (reads Stack A) mov [eax + 16], esp ; old_ctx->esp = current ESP A is FROZEN

THE PIVOT ESP is reassigned (yellow = metamorphosis) asm mov eax, [esp + 28] ; eax = new_ctx ptr (reads Stack A, last time) mov esp, [eax + 16] ; ESP = B->context.esp IDENTITY SWAP ; ; BEFORE: [esp+N] reads Stack A ; AFTER: [esp+N] reads Stack B ; The CPU does not know. The code does not care. ; One register assignment changed everything.

RESTORE PHASE running on Stack B (purple = Stack B) asm popfd ; ESP+=4 Stack B restores B's EFLAGS ; IF=1 interrupts re-enabled! pop ebp ; ESP+=4 Stack B restores B's EBP pop edi ; ESP+=4 Stack B restores B's EDI pop esi ; ESP+=4 Stack B restores B's ESI pop ebx ; ESP+=4 Stack B restores B's EBX ret ; ESP+=4 Stack B pops B's saved EIP ; jumps to: isr_common_stub+N ; which runs iretd user mode Process B

g.text: [ +20 ] SS_user = 0x0023 CPU pushed on interrupt entry
[ +20 ] SS_user = 0x0023 will be popped by iretd
[ +16 ] ESP_user = 0xBFFFFEC8 will be popped by iretd
[ +12 ] EFLAGS = 0x00000202 will be popped by iretd
[ +08 ] CS_user = 0x001B will be popped by iretd
